Package: libmesa-llvmpipe
Submenu: Video
Version: 25.1.6-r1
Depends: +libc +libatomic +libstdcpp +zlib +libdrm +libsensors +libwayland +libzstd +wayland-protocols @MESA_USE_LLVM
Conflicts: 
Menu-Depends: 
Provides: libmesa
Build-Variant: llvmpipe
Section: libs
Category: Libraries
Repository: base
Title: Mesa3D OpenGL and friends (LLVMpipe)
Maintainer: Daniel Golle <daniel@makrotopia.org>
Source: mesa-25.1.6.tar.xz
License: BSD-3-Clause
URL: https://www.mesa3d.org
Type: ipkg
Description: The Gallium LLVMpipe driver is a software rasterizer that uses LLVM to
do runtime code generation. Shaders, point/line/triangle rasterization
and vertex processing are implemented with LLVM IR which is translated
to native CPU machine code. Also, the driver is multithreaded to take
advantage of multiple CPU cores (up to 32 at this time). It's the
fastest software rasterizer for Mesa.
@@

